There's an issue with the second `useEffect` hook. It's missing a closing bracket before the callback function `userId => {`. I believe this is causing the hook to run multiple times and fetch the same data repeatedly. Here's how you can fix it:

```
useEffect(() => {
   if (userId) {
     const userRef = firebase.database().ref(`users/${userId}`);
     userRef.on('value', snapshot => {
       const data = snapshot.val();
       setUserData(data);
     }); // closing bracket was missing here

     const bookedMKRef = firebase.database().ref(`users/${userId}/bookedMK`);
     bookedMKRef.on('value', snapshot => {
       const data = snapshot.val();
       if (data) {
         const mk = Object.values(data);
         setBookedMK(mk);
       } else {
         setBookedMK([]);
       }
     });

     // Cleanup function which will remove the listeners when the component is unmounted
     return () => {
       userRef.off();
       bookedMKRef.off();
     };
   }
}, [userId]);
```

With this fix, the `useEffect` hook should only run once and fetch the data from Firebase correctly. Please let me know if this resolves the issue.

